Personal Finance Tracker
A mobile-friendly web app for tracking personal finances and poker sessions. Data syncs across devices via the cloud — sign in from any browser to see your entries.

Features
Finance Tracker — log income and expenses by category, view spending breakdowns, and export your history to CSV
Recurring Transactions — set up transactions that post automatically on a monthly or custom interval
Poker Tracker — log poker sessions by buy-in, cash-out, and location; winnings and losses sync automatically to your finance tracker
Cloud Sync — all data is tied to your account and available on any device

Getting Started
Open the app and create an account with your email, username, and password
Sign in — your account keeps you signed in indefinitely unless you sign out
If you had existing local data before creating an account, it will be imported automatically on first login

Using the Finance Tracker
Tap Add to log a transaction — choose Income or Expense, enter an amount, category, and date
Check Make this a recurring transaction to set up a repeating entry (monthly by day, or every N days)
Tap History to view past transactions, filter by type or category, and see a spending breakdown chart
Use the Recurring Transactions panel in History to manage or disable recurring entries

Using the Poker Tracker
Log each session with location, buy-in amount, and cash-out amount
Add custom tags to sessions for filtering
Sessions automatically appear as income or expense entries in the Finance Tracker